            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [ ¶ Mr. Raveret-Wattel laid on the table seeds sent from Australia by Baron von Mueller; these are seeds of the  ¶ Atriplex ¶   ¶ spongiosa ¶ , a plant that grows in salt marshes and that is a valu...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">90.03.00a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Casimir Raveret-Wattel</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Revue des sciences naturelles appliquées</seg>, vol. 37 (1890), p. 540. It is dated to March 1890 as the latest likely date that it could have been sent to have been read at the meeting of the Société Nationale d'acclimatation de France held on 25 April 1890.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[M. Raveret-Wattel dépose sur le bureau des graines envoyées d'Australie par le baron von Mueller; ce sont des <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>graines de l'<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Atriplex</seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">spongiosa</seg>, plante qui se développe dans les marais salants, et qui est d'une ressource précieuse <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pour le bétail quand la sécheresse a détruit toute autre végétation.]</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; line-height: 0.1945in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[<seg style="">Mr. Raveret-Wattel laid on the table seeds sent from Australia by Baron von Mueller; these are seeds of the </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Atriplex</seg>
               <seg style=""> </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; ">spongiosa</seg>
               <seg style="">, a plant that grows in salt marshes and that is a valuable resource for livestock when drought has destroyed all other vegetation.]</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Atriplex%20spongiosa">Atriplex spongiosa</name>
            </p>
